Thank you for the times when you acknowledge the variety of bodies that we inhabit and the ways in which we can modify or approach moves. It would be helpful to many of us if you could explicitly remind us that it's perfectly fine to have a wall or chair nearby when standing on one leg. Many of us cannot safely fall to a variety of reasons --not because we're bad sports. :) Thank you! I hope this posting helps others affirm the beauty of our differences, abilities, and journeys.

üß† Law of attraction is where it's at man. It's so powerful. It's unfortunate that the law of attraction has attracted so much criticism based on the incomplete teachings of many self proclaimed gurus or masters that make it seem so mystical and abstract. So many get let down by these "enlightened individuals" who are more snake oil salesman than human beings. But the way you presented here is both encouraging and helpful to so many, and I feel like this discussion/flow is eternally beneficial to anyone who want at least an ideas of what the essence of attraction is.

As Descartes said: "I think, therefore I am." Most of our thoughts are repetitive patterns of the same thing each day, and even most of those thought are trivial thoughts. But what we think about often is what we become. I attract what I think about the most because I become that myself. When we were together over Christmas, my sister convinced me to do your Yoga Camp along with her even though we live no where near one another. I love to run and though I always loved the IDEA of yoga, I never found it particularly worthwhile for myself. These past 26 days have been a struggle for me. My yoga practice was always kind of mashed in somewhere and then I still felt rushed, my brain never for one second really shutting up. I got grumpy when we moved into positions I didn't like or struggled to hold. I faithfully did every single day, but it wasn't something I was really looking forward to, but another thing I HAD to do. 

All that being said, today's practice might have been something of a breakthrough for me. I feel like the 40 minutes were over as soon as they started. I focused on my breathing. I laughed when my cat ran into my face as I stretched. I enjoyed every stretch. I balanced and fell and balanced more. I'm not sure what was different, but today felt absolutely fantastic and I wanted to tell you that. Thank you. I'm hoping this is a change that can last, hoping my brain will continue to allow me to really experience everything these videos offer. Again, thank you.
